{"type":"message","id":"ec8d6f5d","parentId":"250d7c57","timestamp":"2026-02-18T18:51:50.583Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-02-18 20:51 GMT+2] OPERATION: SELF-IMPROVEMENT (DE-BASHIFICATION & RUST INTEGRATION).\n\n1.  **De-Bashification (Scan & Replace):**\n    *   *Scan:* `scripts/*.py`, `src/core/*.py`. Look for `subprocess.run`, `os.system` calling shell tools.\n    *   *Replace:* Use `pathlib.Path`, `shutil.rmtree`.\n    *   *Constraint:* No more `ls`, `grep`, `cat`.\n\n2.  **Immune System Integration:**\n    *   *Edit:* `src/agent_wrapper.py`.\n    *   *Logic:* On startup -> Import `skills.system_doctor.doctor` -> Run `check()`.\n    *   *Guard:* If score < 80 -> `sys.exit(\"SYSTEM UNHEALTHY\")`.\n\n3.  **Rust Integration (Eat Your Own Dog Food):**\n    *   *Edit:* `scripts/log_compressor.py` (or Archivist util).\n    *   *Replace:* `hashlib` calls with `rust_core.validate_checksum` (or add hashing fn to Rust if needed, or just use checksum for dedup).\n    *   *Note:* Using `validate_checksum` as a fast hash proxy.\n\n4.  **Roadmap Update (`docs/ROADMAP_V6.md`):**\n    *   Mark Phase 2 Complete.\n    *   Add Phase 3 Task.\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Count of Bash cmds removed.\n    *   Rust integration verification.\n    *   Roadmap status."}],"timestamp":1771440710580}}
{"type":"message","id":"33432aa0","parentId":"ec8d6f5d","timestamp":"2026-02-18T18:52:10.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Contemplating De-Bash**\n\nI'm currently focused on the \"De-Bash ification\" task. My plan involves scanning Python scripts within specified directories for shell commands. The goal is to identify and replace these calls, particularly those using `subprocess.run` or `os.system` with direct shell commands like `ls` and `grep`. I'm thinking of creating a list of these shell commands and then figuring out the pythonic way to replace them, and then finally refactor the python scripts to replace the usages.\n\n\n**Analyzing Python Scripts**\n\nNow, I'm digging into how to handle the `De-Bash ification` process effectively. I'm focusing on the Python scripts located in `scripts/*.py` and `src/core/*.py`. The initial step involves detecting shell commands within the scripts. I'm working on refining the command detection to accurately pinpoint usages of `subprocess.run`, `os.system` along with those using commands like `ls`, `grep`, and `cat`.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771440729839_13","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path scripts/*.py, src/core/*.py -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771440729952_14","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs/ROADMAP_V6.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771440730066_15","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/agent_wrapper.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771440730192_16","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"scripts/log_compressor.py"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4811,"output":206,"cacheRead":2241,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5017,"cost":{"input":0.009622,"output":0.0024720000000000002,"cacheRead":0.00044820000000000005,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0125422}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771440710583}}
